<br>
There was a tradeskill combine that yielded more when sold than it cost to produce.  Macro programs were written to perform this combine over and over, yielding large sums of platinum.  This pp was then sold on EQ auction sites, and because MM is an older server and harder for new players to establish themselves without some change in their pocketbook, lots of people bought plat cheaply.  Therefore, inflation is rampant.  Even though the tradeskill resale values were corrected and a bit of plat was sucked out of the economy with the casino, other bazaar macros exist that scout traders selling items at reasonable prices, buy them, and mark them up.<br>
<br>
Calli<br>
